# Admin Panel Standards

## Component Structure

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Admin component with TypeScript
interface DriverTableProps {
  drivers: Driver[];
  onEdit: (id: string) => void;
  onDelete: (id: string) => void;
}

export const DriverTable: React.FC<DriverTableProps> = ({ 
  drivers, 
  onEdit, 
  onDelete 
}) => {
  return (
    <DataTable
      columns={columns}
      data={drivers}
      pagination
      responsive
    />
  );
};
```

## Form Handling

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Validated form with error handling
const BookingForm: React.FC = () => {
  const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm({
    resolver: zodResolver(bookingSchema)
  });

  const onSubmit = async (data: BookingInput) => {
    try {
      await api.post('/bookings', data);
      toast.success('Booking created');
      router.push('/bookings');
    } catch (err) {
      toast.error('Failed to create booking');
      logger.error('Form submission error', err);
    }
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
      <Input 
        {...register('pickupLocation')} 
        error={errors.pickupLocation?.message}
      />
      <Button type="submit">Create</Button>
    </form>
  );
};
```

## Data Tables

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Data table with actions and pagination
const columns = [
  { field: 'id', headerName: 'ID', width: 100 },
  { field: 'name', headerName: 'Driver Name', width: 200 },
  { field: 'phone', headerName: 'Phone', width: 150 },
  { field: 'status', headerName: 'Status', width: 120,
    renderCell: (params) => (
      <StatusBadge status={params.value} />
    )
  },
  { field: 'actions', headerName: 'Actions', width: 150,
    renderCell: (params) => (
      <ActionButtons 
        onEdit={() => handleEdit(params.row.id)}
        onDelete={() => handleDelete(params.row.id)}
      />
    )
  }
];
```

## Dashboard Metrics

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Dashboard card with real-time data
const MetricsCard: React.FC<{ title: string; value: number }> = ({ 
  title, 
  value 
}) => {
  const [data, setData] = useState(value);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    const interval = setInterval(async () => {
      const updated = await fetchMetric(title);
      setData(updated);
    }, 30000); // Refresh every 30 seconds
    
    return () => clearInterval(interval);
  }, [title]);

  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>{title}</CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <Typography variant="h3">{data}</Typography>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
};
```

## Role-Based Access

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Protected admin routes
const ProtectedRoute: React.FC<{ 
  children: React.ReactNode;
  requiredRole: 'admin' | 'superadmin';
}> = ({ children, requiredRole }) => {
  const { user, loading } = useAuth();
  
  if (loading) return <LoadingSpinner />;
  
  if (!user || user.role !== requiredRole) {
    return <Navigate to="/unauthorized" />;
  }
  
  return <>{children}</>;
};
```

## Required Practices

- Use data tables with sorting/filtering (Material-UI, Ant Design, shadcn/ui)
- Implement form validation with react-hook-form + Zod
- Add loading states for all async operations
- Show success/error toasts for user actions
- Implement role-based access control (RBAC)
- Add search and filters for data tables
- Export data to CSV/Excel functionality
- Implement audit logs for admin actions
- Use charts for analytics (Recharts, Chart.js)
- Optimize large data sets with pagination
- Add confirmation modals for destructive actions
- Implement real-time updates where needed (WebSocket/polling)
